The National Leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Bola Tinubu, has again denied having investment in the Lekki toll gate in Lagos State. Tinubu, in a statement on Sunday, also said that if the toll gate is reopened, revenues should be donated to victims of last Tuesday’s shooting. “At the bottom, the toll gate is a public asset. If it is reopened, revenues should be donated to the confirmed victims of the Lekki attack as well as to other identifiable victims of police brutality in Lagos. “Let government use the money to compensate and take care of those who have lost life or limb in the struggle for all citizens to go about the quiet, peaceful enjoyment of life at peaceful End SARS protesters at the Lekki toll gate on Tuesday, October 20.